<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Both indumentum and leaf shape vary considerably in this species as in the related 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bonariensis">Ipomoea bonariensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Leaves are usually entire but 3-lobed forms occur occasionally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oranensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. oranensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has stellate hairs but they are never obvious as in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bonariensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. bonariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and are often difficult to find, most hairs being simple. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oranensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea oranensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exserta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. exserta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the two species are almost indistinguishable when not in flower. However, the funnel-shaped corolla of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oranensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. oranensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is totally different from the hypocrateriform corolla of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exserta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. exserta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its exserted stamens.
</paragraph>
